<protolog id="rid.288_nm.614" type="description" xmlns="http://namesforlife.com/ns/protolog" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://namesforlife.com/ns/protolog file:/C:/NamesforLife/workspace/namesforlife-schema/protolog.xsd"><organism doi="10.1601/nm.614" rank="genus">Flexistipes</organism><reference id="rid.288"><citation citation-type="journal"><authors><person-name><surname>Fiala</surname><given-names>G.</given-names></person-name><person-name><surname>Woese</surname><given-names>C.R.</given-names></person-name><person-name><surname>Langworthy</surname><given-names>T.A.</given-names></person-name><person-name><surname>Stetter</surname><given-names>K.O.</given-names></person-name></authors><article-title>Flexistipes sinusarabici, a novel genus and species of eubacteria occurring in the Atlantis II Deep brines of the Red Sea</article-title><year>1990</year><volume>154</volume><fpage>120</fpage><lpage>126</lpage><source id="118">Archives of Microbiology</source><abbrev>Arch Microbiol</abbrev><issn>0302-8933</issn><essn>1432-072X</essn><pub-id pub-id-type="doi">10.1007/BF00423320</pub-id></citation></reference><content><p class="title"><s>Description of <i>Flexistipes</i>, Fiala, Woese, Langworthy, and Stetter, gen. nov.</s></p><p class="etymology"><s><i>Flexistipes</i> (Fle.xi.sti'pes M.L. masc. n. <i>flexus</i> winding; M.L. masc. n. <i>stipes</i> stick; M.L. masc. n. <i>Flexistipes</i> the flexible stick)</s></p><p class="description"><s>Non-motile, flexible rods.</s><s>No spores formed.</s><s>Halophilic, neutrophilic, and slightly thermophilic.</s><s>Heterotrophic growth under anaerobic conditions.</s><s>Gram-negative.</s><s>Muramic acid and mesodiaminopimelic acid present.</s><s>Ester lipids in the cytoplasmic membrane.</s><s>G+C around 39 mol%.</s><s>Groups with the general cluster of eubacterial phyla by 16S rRNA analyses.</s><s>No specific relation to any phylum so far described.</s></p></content></protolog>